---
import Page from '~/layouts/Page.astro';
import DownloadButton from '~/components/DownloadButton.astro';
import { VERSION } from '~/lib/releases';
---

<Page
  title="DataSUS ETL — Brazilian public-health data, made workable"
  description="A free, open-source desktop app that downloads, converts, and organizes DATASUS data so you can actually use it."
  locale="en"
  ptPath="/"
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pt-16 md:pt-28 pb-20">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1.4fr_1fr] gap-16 items-end">
        <div>
          <p class="rise stamp text-clinic-red">Edition v{VERSION} · Apache 2.0</p>
          <h1 class="rise rise-d1 display-serif mt-4 text-display-xl text-ink">
            Public-health data,<br />
            <em class="italic font-normal text-ink-600">made workable</em>.
          </h1>
          <p class="rise rise-d2 mt-8 text-lead text-ink-800 max-w-[52ch]">
            DataSUS ETL downloads, converts, and organizes the raw files the
            Brazilian Ministry of Health publishes on its FTP — the ones most
            researchers spend a week fighting before they can even open a
            spreadsheet. One installer. One button. Parquet out the other
            end.
          </p>
          <div class="rise rise-d3 mt-10 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-6">
            <DownloadButton locale="en" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Marginalia / sidenote -->
        <aside class="rise rise-d4 relative lg:pl-10 lg:border-l lg:border-ink/20 mt-10 lg:mt-0">
          <div class="stamp text-ink-400">Field note</div>
          <blockquote class="mt-3 display-serif italic text-ink text-2xl leading-snug">
            “Half an epidemiologist's time is spent parsing DBCs
            that shouldn't exist in 2026.”
          </blockquote>
          <div class="mt-4 text-xs text-ink-400 stamp">— why this project exists</div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Ticker rule -->
    <div class="rise rise-d5 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
      <div class="hairline"></div>
      <div class="py-4 flex flex-wrap gap-x-10 gap-y-2 stamp text-ink-400">
        <span>SIHSUS · Hospital records</span>
        <span class="text-clinic-red">SIM · Mortality</span>
        <span>SIASUS · Ambulatory (WIP)</span>
        <span class="ml-auto">Windows · macOS · Linux</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hairline"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT IT DOES -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 mt-24">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
      <div class="md:col-span-4">
        <p class="stamp text-clinic-red">§ 01</p>
        <h2 class="display-serif mt-2 text-display-lg text-ink">What it does</h2>
        <p class="mt-5 text-ink-600 leading-relaxed max-w-prose-wide">
          Four stages, one command. No Python to install. No DuckDB to
          configure. No one-off PowerShell scripts from a forum in 2014.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-8 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-px bg-ink/10">
        {[
          ['01', 'Downloads', 'Pulls DBC files straight from the DATASUS FTP. You pick state and date range.'],
          ['02', 'Converts', 'DBC → DBF → DuckDB → Parquet, all in-process. No CSV detours, no intermediate junk.'],
          ['03', 'Enriches', 'Joins IBGE municipal codes (5,571 municipalities) and CID mappings automatically.'],
          ['04', 'Exposes', 'Browse with the UI, query with DuckDB SQL, or read the partitioned parquet from anywhere.'],
        ].map(([n, title, body]) => (
          <article class="bg-paper-50 p-6 md:p-8">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-clinic-red text-sm">{n}</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="display-serif text-display text-ink leading-tight">{title}</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-ink-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">{body}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TWO AUDIENCES -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 mt-32">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 items-start">
      <div class="md:col-span-4">
        <p class="stamp text-clinic-red">§ 02</p>
        <h2 class="display-serif mt-2 text-display-lg text-ink">For two kinds of user</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-8 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="marker">
          <h3 class="display-serif text-display text-ink">Researchers · clinicians</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-ink-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Install, click the shortcut, pick a folder, choose a subsystem
            and a date range. The app downloads and processes everything
            locally. Then you query through the web UI with dropdowns and
            filters — no SQL required.
          </p>
          <a href="./tutorial/" class="stamp mt-4 inline-block prose-editorial">Read the tutorial →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="marker">
          <h3 class="display-serif text-display text-ink">Developers · data teams</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-ink-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            The same installer exposes the full <code class="font-mono text-ink">datasus</code>
            CLI to your shell (opt-in PATH checkbox). Scriptable pipelines,
            a Python API, and DuckDB as the query surface — read the
            partitioned parquet from polars, pandas, R, anything.
          </p>
          <a href="./docs/" class="stamp mt-4 inline-block prose-editorial">Read the docs →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CALLOUT -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 mt-32">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 items-end">
      <div class="md:col-span-7">
        <p class="stamp text-clinic-red">§ 03 — Download</p>
        <h2 class="display-serif mt-2 text-display-lg text-ink">
          Ready when you are.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-5 text-ink-600 leading-relaxed max-w-prose-wide">
          The button detects your operating system. The full list, with
          checksums, lives on the download page. Releases are cut from the
          <code class="font-mono text-ink">VERSION</code> file in the repo — the
          same number is shown in the app footer and printed by
          <code class="font-mono text-ink">datasus version</code>.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8"><DownloadButton locale="en" /></div>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-5">
        <div class="border border-ink/15 bg-paper-50 p-6">
          <div class="stamp text-ink-400">Known expectations</div>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-800">
            <li>— First launch: ~20s to warm up parquet indexes.</li>
            <li>— Installer is unsigned. A one-time “More info → Run anyway”
              click on Windows; “right-click Open” on macOS.</li>
            <li>— SIM publishes with a ~2-year lag — the app tells you.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Page>
